Everton could yet face action from the Football Association after a supporter appeared to shine a laser towards the eye of Stoke City’s Bojan Krkic during the Boxing Day defeat at Goodison Park.

Images emerged after the match that demonstrated a green light hovering over the Stoke forward’s eye as he stepped up to score the penalty kick that secured the three points for Mark Hughes’ side.

It is understood that the player was not aware of the light at the time and didn't appear to be distracted as he put the ball beyond Tim Howard into the bottom left corner.   

