The penalty was already a controversial one for Everton, with the Toffees players protesting to referee Lee Mason that Spaniard Bojan went down too easily under the challenge of James McCarthy. 

Everton's Boxing Day loss was their second in a row and the 3-2 defeat by Newcastle on Sunday made it three as they slipped four points behind 11th-placed Stoke, who beat West Brom.  

